cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.LO, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with regular languages and their complexity measures, such as state complexity, syntactic semigroup, and maximal complexities of atoms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). The paper also involves combinatorial and graph-theoretic arguments, which suggest possible sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The paper also uses some algebraic concepts, such as semigroups, which could place it in cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
